1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:04,433
[PENSIVE]

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,300
My child!

3
00:00:09,433 --> 00:00:10,900
Ashley, what happened to you?

4
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:11,900
- Ashley!
- Wait.

5
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:12,967
Patient is unresponsive.

6
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:14,367
Code blue!

7
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,400
I don't know what to do anymore
when you're gone.

8
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:17,967
You are all I have, my child.

9
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,000
This is your fault!

10
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:20,700
- This is your fault!
- Thea!

11
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:23,833
What was Sir Edward's fault?

12
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:26,000
Sir Edward is not
the one at fault.

13
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,333
It was Ma'am Regina.

14
00:00:27,467 --> 00:00:29,167
Sir Greg believed

15
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:32,267
that Sir Edward was Ma'am
Regina's child with another man.

16
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,867
I hope you are doing well,
Walter.

17
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:38,100
Even if you do not say it,

18
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,800
I already know everything,

19
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,067
Regina.

20
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,667
About your affair
with my father.

21
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:44,967
And about your child.

22
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,200
[WALTER WHIMPERING]

23
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,400
[MACHINE BEEPING]

24
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:41,200
[DRAMATIC]

25
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:45,367
My God!

26
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,933
Please have mercy!

27
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,767
Heal my child!

28
00:01:58,633 --> 00:01:59,800
I will change for the better.

29
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:01,800
I will obey everything You
ask me to do

30
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:03,967
just let Ashley be okay.

31
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:06,933
Have mercy!

32
00:02:07,067 --> 00:02:08,500
My God!

33
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,767
[SOBBING]

34
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:21,067
[INTENSE]

35
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,067
My child?

36
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,700
- [MACHINE BEEPING]
- My child!

37
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,267
Ashley!

38
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,700
Ash, what's happening?

39
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:29,733
What's happening?

40
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:31,900
What is happening to you,
my child?

41
00:02:32,033 --> 00:02:34,400
- Wait! Wait!
- What is happening?

42
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:36,200
- Edward!
- Nurse!

43
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,367
My child!

44
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,733
My child, what is happening
to you?

45
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,300
My child!

46
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,967
So, Ma'am Regina
also has secrets?

47
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:50,667
I thought Sir Greg was the only
one with scandals.

48
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,700
I have been here
for a long time now,

49
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,867
and I only just learned
about these rumors.

50
00:02:54,967 --> 00:02:57,833
Yes, but you know,
I did not witness it myself too.

51
00:02:57,967 --> 00:02:58,900
I only remember that

52
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:02,567
because Ms. Yolly mentioned it
to me briefly.

53
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:06,300
Sir Greg is extremely harsh
toward Sir Edward.

54
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:09,067
You know, when I saw them
on TV,

55
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:12,300
I thought they were
a happy family.

56
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:13,700
A perfect family.

57
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:14,833
Of course,

58
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:18,200
that is what they want
the audience to see.

59
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,300
[SIGHS]

60
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:24,500
Happy, united, powerful.

61
00:03:24,667 --> 00:03:27,833
But once they're seen
to have cracks,

62
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:32,333
they think they'll appear weak
in the eyes of others,

63
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:34,667
in the world they move in.

64
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,000
Oh, my!

65
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,000
It is shocking that
this happens.

66
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:42,300
Being wealthy
is not easy after all.

67
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:43,633
But Ms. Yolly,

68
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:48,467
what exactly did
Sir Edward do to Sir Greg?

69
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,667
Sir Edward was not at fault.

70
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,100
It was Ma'am Regina.

71
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,133
What?

72
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,767
Sir Greg believed

73
00:03:56,900 --> 00:04:00,133
Sir Edward was Ma'am Regina's
child with another man.

74
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,733
That means...

75
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:07,567
Ma'am Regina had a lover?

76
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:09,700
That explains it.

77
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:12,000
Sir Greg wouldn't act that way
toward them

78
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,833
if there weren't an issue.

79
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:18,467
You know, Ms. Yolly said that
this family has so many secrets.

80
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,867
Hey, I did not say that.

81
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,333
I said that is what
Sir Greg believes.

82
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:26,967
Maybe that is why he treats
the youngest that way.

83
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:31,000
Maybe the rumors are true.

84
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:33,300
But why would
Ma'am Regina get mad?

85
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:37,900
Wasn't she furious about
the rumors about Sir Greg?

86
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:40,133
Such a hypocrite.

87
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:41,367
Who knows.

88
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:44,333
Maybe she wants to get even.

89
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:45,800
My god!

90
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:47,200
Think about it.

91
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:51,033
Do you think Ma'am Regina
is getting revenge?

92
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:53,767
I don't know anymore. There's a
lot happening inside this house.

93
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,400
This house is a mess.

94
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:56,267
I agree.

95
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,167
[DRAMATIC TENSE]

96
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:11,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:19,500
<i>I hope you are doing well,
Walter.</i>

98
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:21,533
[SOBBING]

99
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:25,467
<i>I am so sorry
for what I did to you.</i>

100
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:29,600
[SOBBING]

101
00:06:32,733 --> 00:06:34,467
My child, what is happening
to you?

102
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,067
Edward!

103
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:36,700
Excuse me.

104
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,167
- Doc?
- Ashley?

105
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,233
- What's happening to my child?
- Ashley?

106
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:41,267
Patient is not responding.

107
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:43,167
Check her blood pressure.

108
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,267
BP is eighty over sixty, Doc.

109
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,067
Start epinephrine drip.

110
00:06:48,467 --> 00:06:50,000
My child!

111
00:06:53,367 --> 00:06:56,800
Doctor, what is happening
to my child?

112
00:06:56,933 --> 00:06:58,033
Ashley!

113
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,167
- [MACHINE BEEPING]
- Ashley, my child.

114
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:03,433
[SOBBING]

115
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:06,033
Doc...

116
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,767
Doctor, save my child.

117
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,000
Do not let her die!

118
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:11,433
The patient
is in septic shock.

119
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:12,500
We need to call the ICU.

120
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,700
We need more...
[SPEAKS INDISTINCLY]

121
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,433
My child.

122
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:19,167
No pulse, no breathing.

123
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,933
Code blue, Team! Code blue!

124
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:22,333
Blue!

125
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:25,300
Start CPR! Ambu bag!

126
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:26,733
[SOBBING]

127
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:28,100
Epinephrine.

128
00:07:28,233 --> 00:07:31,967
Do not let her die, please.

129
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,433
Epinephrine ready.

130
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:38,967
Pulse check! Rhythm check!

131
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,767
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

132
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:44,867
Still has no pulse.

133
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,400
Resume CPR!

134
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,933
Do not leave us yet,
my child.

135
00:07:55,067 --> 00:07:57,033
I don't know what to do anymore
when you're gone.

136
00:07:57,167 --> 00:07:58,933
You are all I have!

137
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:01,233
Please.

138
00:08:01,367 --> 00:08:03,133
[INTENSE]

139
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,933
Pulse check! Rhythm check!

140
00:08:06,067 --> 00:08:11,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

141
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:12,767
Pulse check! Rythm check!

142
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:14,567
[FLATLINE BEEPING]

143
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,233
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

144
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:17,933
Doctor.

145
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:19,500
Patient has pulse.

146
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,733
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

147
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:26,400
The patient needs to be
transferred to the ICU.

148
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:31,767
I will make sure that every tear
we cry today...

149
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:36,800
will be paid for by the people
who did this to you, my child.

150
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:39,933
Ma'am, we have a pulse.

151
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:41,233
Your child's condition
is critical.

152
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:44,000
We need to transfer her
to the ICU right now.

153
00:08:44,133 --> 00:08:48,067
[SOBBING]

154
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:52,133
[INTENSE]

155
00:09:00,367 --> 00:09:01,733
Mrs. Torrecampo.

156
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:04,633
Well, nice to see you here
again.

157
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,433
Judging by the liquor
in your glass,

158
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:09,833
it looks like you are going
through something again.

159
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:13,733
Is this about your sick
grandchild?

160
00:09:13,867 --> 00:09:17,367
[PENSIVE]

161
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:23,400
I wish it were just that,
but...

162
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,433
I have other problems too,
Aldrin.

163
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,533
- May I?
- Yes.

164
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:35,333
Well, if you don't mind me
asking,

165
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:38,000
did you fight
with Sir Greg again?

166
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:41,233
He keeps bringing up our past.

167
00:09:41,367 --> 00:09:46,833
Something that I thought
was forgotten and forgiven.

168
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:49,667
And what did you do?

169
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:54,033
You don't have to say anything.

170
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:55,200
I understand.

171
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:59,033
I do not want to revisit
my past.

172
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:02,467
Especially those who have
already moved on.

173
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:06,667
[INTENSE]

174
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:16,867
It's okay, Sir,

175
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,800
- so you can recover quickly.
- [GROANS]

176
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:20,867
Do you want to recover quickly?

177
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:27,400
Are you feeling pain anywhere?

178
00:10:27,533 --> 00:10:28,967
What are you feeling?

179
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:33,333
[TENSE]

180
00:10:42,967 --> 00:10:44,367
Nurse, leave us.

181
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:48,633
I will leave you
for a moment, Sir.

182
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:56,167
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:06,600
[TENSE]

184
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:21,133
<i> Even if you don't say it...</i>

185
00:11:22,967 --> 00:11:25,133
<i> I already know everything...</i>

186
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:26,533
<i> Regina.</i>

187
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:30,900
<i>About your affair
with my father.</i>

188
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:33,700
<i> And about your child.</i>

189
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:38,567
- [WALTER WHIMPERING]
- [INTENSE]

190
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:42,000
[WHIMPERING]

191
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:57,533
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:08,600
Mom...

193
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:11,833
can we visit Ashley
before we leave?

194
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:19,100
Jasmine, you know it's still
complicated with her parents.

195
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:20,433
Maybe...

196
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:22,367
not now.

197
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,433
I just wanted to make sure
that she's okay.

198
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,733
Once things calm down,

199
00:12:28,867 --> 00:12:31,333
we'll visit Ashley then.

200
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:34,233
But for now, let's go home.

201
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,167
Sir Paolo,

202
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,667
Ma'am Marj.

203
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,000
I passed by the nurse station.

204
00:12:45,133 --> 00:12:47,667
I heard there's a problem
with Ashley.

205
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:53,467
[INTENSE]

206
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,100
How is Ashley?

207
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:04,767
Where is she?

208
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,400
What are you doing here?

209
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,500
How is she?

210
00:13:09,633 --> 00:13:10,800
Well...

211
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:13,333
she almost died
because of what you did.

212
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:16,967
Thea, I'm sorry, we did not
expect this to happen.

213
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:20,767
Do you know what I want
to do to you right now?

214
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:24,200
I want to drag you out
of the hospital.

215
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:27,167
And humiliate you in public.

216
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:30,000
Just like what you did
to me before.

217
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:32,300
But you know
what's the difference?

218
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:34,800
I was just a cheater.

219
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:35,833
You...

220
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:39,233
the two of you, are killers.

221
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:42,233
Thea, we are not here
to fight.

222
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:43,967
We are here to help.

223
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,300
[HUFFS]

224
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:46,667
For what?

225
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,767
To wash your hands of guilt?

226
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,500
To make yourselves
look like the good ones

227
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:52,333
and the saviors of my child?

228
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:56,467
This is your fault.

229
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,000
- This is your fault.
- Thea.

230
00:13:58,133 --> 00:13:59,800
- This is your fault.
- Thea.

231
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:00,867
Please.

232
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:01,967
Stop it.

233
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:02,867
Don't engage with them.

234
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,367
We'll hold them
accountable later.

235
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,367
But now,

236
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,467
we have to stay calm
for our daughter.

237
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:14,967
Do not go near my child again!

238
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:17,867
Get out.

239
00:14:18,967 --> 00:14:19,967
Leave!

240
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:30,067
[INTENSE]

241
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:46,100
[MACHINE BEEPING]

242
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,667
Mom.

243
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,700
I'm sorry, I made
you and dad worry.

244
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:56,600
Now, you understand, my child,

245
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:59,733
why we did not want you
to donate.

246
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:01,267
If you had not let them
manipulate you,

247
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,867
you would not be here.

248
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:06,500
Look at you, you are the one
suffering now.

249
00:15:06,633 --> 00:15:11,400
[INTENSE]

250
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:24,300
Why?

251
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:28,533
Mom...

252
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:30,833
I can't feel my legs.

253
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:33,133
[GASPS]

254
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:34,300
What?

255
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,733
This, can you feel this?

256
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:39,467
This? Can you feel it,
my child?

257
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,400
No.

258
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:42,667
My child.

259
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,600
Mom, I thought
it was just numbness.

260
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:46,333
It's been a while.

261
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,867
I can't move them, Mom.

262
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,100
[INTENSE]

263
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,167
After the harvest
from the iliac crest,

264
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:12,633
it is possible that an abscess
or pus formed around the area

265
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:15,100
that could have affected
Ashley's nerves.

266
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:20,067
Is that the reason why
she cannot feel her legs?

267
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:22,867
Yes, we need to remove
the abscess

268
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:25,133
to prevent further infection.

269
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:29,167
Also, so her condition
does not worsen.

270
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,700
Are you saying that
if she is not operated on,

271
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:34,167
my child will not be able
to walk?

272
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,267
That is correct, Ma'am.

273
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,900
- [SIGHS]
- Let us know

274
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:39,567
when do you want
to do the surgery,

275
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,133
but I suggest you do it
as soon as possible

276
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:45,433
because time
is very essential.

277
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:46,900
Excuse me.

278
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,433
Edward, what are we going
to do?

279
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:55,667
That will cost a lot.

280
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,500
We are completely drained.

281
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:04,367
Maybe ask Paolo for money
for the surgery?

282
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,600
As compensation
for what they did to Ashley.

283
00:17:09,033 --> 00:17:10,333
No.

284
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:12,900
I will not go to anyone
in my family.

285
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,133
And what?

286
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:17,267
You will just let Ashley
be disabled for life

287
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:18,967
because of your pride?

288
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:20,300
No.

289
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,567
I will not go to them.

290
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,633
If we accept their money,

291
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,967
they will hold it
over us forever.

292
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,133
We will belong to them.

293
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,633
I will find a way.

294
00:17:37,367 --> 00:17:38,700
I will handle it.

295
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,333
- Paolo!
- Sorry, Ma'am!

296
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,033
- Come out!
- You are not allowed here.

297
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:52,667
- Sorry, Ma'am.
- Open the gate!

298
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,000
- Ma'am, Ma'am! Ma'am Thea.
- You have no shame!

299
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:56,900
Ma'am Thea, please do not cause
a scene here.

300
00:17:57,033 --> 00:17:59,733
If you do not let me in,
I will tear this gate down!

301
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:01,567
-You're not allowed here, Ma'am.
-Marj! Paolo!

302
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:02,700
- Open this gate!
- Ma'am!

303
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:03,833
Ma'am, you're not allowed here.

304
00:18:03,967 --> 00:18:04,933
- I'm sorry.
- Let me in!

305
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:07,800
Tell your employers
that I am here.

306
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:10,200
- Thea, stop this.
- Marj!

307
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:13,367
I'm sorry, Ma'am. We are just
following orders.

308
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:15,233
- Open this gate!
- You're not allowed to come in.

309
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:17,900
Paolo!

310
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:20,733
Talk to me. Let's talk it out!

311
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:22,600
- Open this gate!
- Sorry, Ma'am.

312
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,400
You're not allowed to come in.

313
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:25,667
I will not stop!

314
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,533
If not, I will destroy
this gate.

315
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:28,900
Let her in, Oscar.

316
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:30,933
Damn it!

317
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,767
Stop it! You are embarrassing us
in front of the neighbors.

318
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:38,167
Why? Are you ashamed they might
hear what you did to my child?

319
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:41,233
Don't worry, I will be quick.

320
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:44,233
Once I collect what you owe,
I will leave.

321
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:46,167
What are you talking about?

322
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:49,167
Since it's your fault
that Ashley was harmed,

323
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:52,000
you will pay for her surgery.

324
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:55,367
Marj, after all,
you have the money, right?

325
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:58,767
You are the one benefiting
from being a Torrecampo.

326
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:01,867
Make sure that you'll fix this.

327
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,700
Because if something bad
happens to my child,

328
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,233
if she doesn't get better,

329
00:19:05,367 --> 00:19:06,767
you will pay for it.

330
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:08,667
I will sue you!

331
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,200
Especially you, Paolo.

332
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:14,433
[INTENSE]

333
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:19,400
Thea, wait,
let's talk about this.

334
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,467
Thea!

335
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:30,567
[INTENSE]

336
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:40,500
- Thank you very much, Sir.
- Thank you, Mr. Castelo.

337
00:19:40,633 --> 00:19:41,700
I look forward to doing
business with you.

338
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,300
- Same here.
- It was a pleasure.

339
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:46,667
Let's head
to the country club.

340
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,400
It's so worth it.

341
00:19:48,533 --> 00:19:49,767
Well,

342
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,767
what did I tell you?

343
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,833
Make sure you draft
all our contracts.

344
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:57,100
Anything that we can use
with them...

345
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:58,900
We have to sign, okay?

346
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,100
Aldrin.

347
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:02,800
[INTENSE]

348
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:04,133
Edward.

349
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,867
Aren't they from Washington
Builders?

350
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,000
Why are you meeting up
with them?

351
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:17,333
[CLEARS THROAT]

352
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:19,400
Guys, will you please excuse us
for a moment?

353
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:24,300
[INTENSE]

354
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:31,733
Edward...

355
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:38,333
they will help the company build
our biggest project yet.

356
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,900
The Asian Business Complex.

357
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,700
Wait.

358
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:48,267
Didn't dad reject them before?

359
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,733
They want to handle
the project themselves.

360
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:54,300
Our people will lose their jobs.

361
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:55,800
And so what?

362
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:58,700
What matters...

363
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,533
is the company will profit.

364
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,633
You know, Edward...

365
00:21:05,767 --> 00:21:07,600
your father is old.

366
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,600
He no longer understands
the benefits

367
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:14,233
of opportunities like these.

368
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:19,900
Wait.

369
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,600
Fine, do what you want.

370
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,567
I do not care about dad anyway.

371
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:28,900
He cut me off.

372
00:21:31,067 --> 00:21:32,433
I am just here because...

373
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:36,367
I wanted to ask for your help.

374
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:39,467
Why?

375
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:41,800
What is your problem?

376
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:46,067
My child.

377
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:48,733
She needs surgery immediately.

378
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:50,933
I need the funds for it.

379
00:21:51,067 --> 00:21:54,600
The doctor said your vitals
are stable again.

380
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:56,433
You will be moved
to a regular room

381
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,367
while waiting for surgery.

382
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:00,900
Do not worry, my child.

383
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:02,967
Your father and I
are doing everything

384
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:05,167
to get you operated on
as soon as possible.

385
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:07,067
So you can walk again.

386
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,967
Thank you, Mom.

387
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:16,033
And I'm sorry if I caused you
and dad even more problems.

388
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:20,067
I know you are already
going through so much.

389
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:23,367
I just added to it.

390
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,533
My child,

391
00:22:24,667 --> 00:22:27,000
do not say that.

392
00:22:27,133 --> 00:22:29,600
It is not your fault
that you became a victim.

393
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:34,433
This is all the fault
of those greedy people.

394
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:37,733
People without conscience
who used you.

395
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:44,733
[DRAMATIC]

396
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,067
I tried contacting
all of my friends, but...

397
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,000
the funds raised
are still not enough.

398
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,367
Aldrin...

399
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:54,767
will you help me?

400
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,967
I'm sorry, Edward.

401
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:03,400
I cannot help you with that.

402
00:23:06,167 --> 00:23:07,800
Wait.

403
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:08,867
Why?

404
00:23:10,533 --> 00:23:14,767
Maybe you are forgetting
what I did to help you.

405
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,567
And now you are leaving me
hanging?

406
00:23:18,967 --> 00:23:20,833
Let's just say...

407
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:23,067
that I already got
what I wanted...

408
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:25,833
and I no longer need you.

409
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,033
It is not my fault...

410
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:32,500
if you are already useless...

411
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:33,633
and still foolish.

412
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:40,700
[THUDDING]

413
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:43,133
You bastard!

414
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:46,567
- [THUDDING]
- [GRUNTS]

415
00:23:48,133 --> 00:23:49,433
Remember this!

416
00:23:51,567 --> 00:23:54,300
You will regret
what you did to me!

417
00:23:54,433 --> 00:24:01,500
[INTENSE]

418
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:15,700
What is that?

419
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,067
Can I use my phone, Mom?

420
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,933
Just for a bit,

421
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,767
I just want to check on Jas.

422
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:24,767
[SIGHS]

423
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:27,167
Ashley, stop it.

424
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:31,367
Didn't I tell you already to cut
off communication with Jasmine?

425
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:33,967
Instead of worrying about her,

426
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:36,667
focus on yourself.

427
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,100
I'm sorry, Mom.

428
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:41,300
I just miss Jas.

429
00:24:42,767 --> 00:24:43,633
My child,

430
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:45,133
what is wrong with you?

431
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,367
Did you suddenly forget?

432
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:52,000
Did you forget that you are here
because of them?

433
00:24:53,467 --> 00:24:56,000
Mom, Jas did nothing wrong.

434
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:59,467
But she is still the child
of the people who harmed you.

435
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:02,233
So you should be angry
at them.

436
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:05,000
While you are worrying
about Jasmine being okay,

437
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:07,667
she's there, in a big mansion.

438
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,567
Her family is complete,
laughing together,

439
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:16,233
while we are drowning
in problems.

440
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:27,700
[DRAMATIC]

441
00:25:43,733 --> 00:25:44,600
Why is it like this?

442
00:25:44,733 --> 00:25:45,800
I was the one who cheated.

443
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:47,433
I was the one who messed up.

444
00:25:47,567 --> 00:25:49,467
Why are my children the ones
being punished?

445
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:50,967
It should have been me.

446
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,367
Paolo, enough.

447
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:54,633
This time, Ashley needs you.

448
00:25:54,767 --> 00:25:56,767
I will not abandon
my other child.

449
00:25:56,900 --> 00:26:00,800
I won't let her live the rest
of her life in a wheelchair.

450
00:26:00,933 --> 00:26:02,000
How about Paolo?

451
00:26:02,133 --> 00:26:03,700
No matter what he does,
even when he makes mistakes,

452
00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:05,333
you are always there
to help him.

453
00:26:05,467 --> 00:26:06,667
What did I do to you?

454
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,600
It feels like I am not
your real child.

455
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:09,800
Do you want to know why?

456
00:26:09,933 --> 00:26:10,867
I want to know.

457
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,467
You want the truth?

458
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:14,000
Because of you,

459
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:16,000
my entire family
was destroyed!

460
00:26:16,133 --> 00:26:18,933
I will destroy...

461
00:26:19,067 --> 00:26:20,600
and I will ruin...

462
00:26:20,733 --> 00:26:22,833
your entire family!

463
00:26:22,967 --> 00:26:24,700
Mark my words.

464
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,433
You are not the only one
who gets to decide this, Aldrin.

465
00:26:27,567 --> 00:26:31,233
If from the beginning
you ran the company properly,

466
00:26:31,367 --> 00:26:32,800
we would not be here.

467
00:26:32,933 --> 00:26:34,800
And where is the family
you're talking about now?

468
00:26:34,933 --> 00:26:38,033
If only you treated me
like a child even once,

469
00:26:38,167 --> 00:26:39,900
I would not have turned
against you!

470
00:26:40,033 --> 00:26:41,100
Shut your mouth!

471
00:26:41,233 --> 00:26:42,767
There is still a lot
that you do not know about.

472
00:26:42,933 --> 00:26:45,500
He is not a real Torrecampo.
